@Steve L the working definition for Natick I picked up just from reading comments here is two proper nouns that cross. The fun with language is that it's how it's used not how it was meant to be used. Your definition is interesting but not really what I've seen. 

I don't interpret the critique as trying to shift blame. I just see it (and agree with) as pointing out that proper noun crossings aren't great design. Having to guess a letter isn't fun or puzzling. What's a gimme name for some won't be for all. 

I think for some the fun of a puzzle is using logic to solve. Others I think enjoy the rote memorization and recall of names. Naticks (proper noun crossings) frustrate the first group.

